Item 7.  Management’s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations
OVERVIEW
NEE’ s operating performance is driven primaril y by the operations of its two principal businesses, FPL, which serves more than 5.7 million
customer accounts in Florida and is one of the largest electric utilities in the U.S., and NEER, which together with affiliated entities is the world's
largest generator of renewable energy from the wind and sun based on 2021 MWh produced on a net generation basis. The table below presents
net income (loss)  attributable  to NEE and earnings (loss) per share attribut able to NEE, assuming dilution, by reportable segment, the FPL
